.TH "amdgpu_dma_buf_begin_cpu_access" 9 "amdgpu_dma_buf_begin_cpu_access" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdgpu_dma_buf_begin_cpu_access \- &dma_buf_ops.begin_cpu_access implementation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" amdgpu_dma_buf_begin_cpu_access
.BI "(struct dma_buf *dma_buf "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction direction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dma_buf" 12
Shared DMA buffer
.IP "direction" 12
Direction of DMA transfer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is called before CPU access to the shared DMA buffer's memory. If it's
a read access, the buffer is moved to the GTT domain if possible, for optimal
CPU read performance.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
